courses.learning_outcomes:
By the end of the course, students will be able to

1. comprehend and discuss selected texts related to science, technology and nature;
2. identify the essential characteristics of how human beings view Nature;
3. formulate informed personal views on the societal implications of scientific explorations;
4. relate the developments in natural sciences highlighted in the course to contemporary human conditions;
5. evaluate the scopes of application, achievements and limitations of highlighted scientific methods.
